559
00:35:22,680 --> 00:35:23,875
He was nodding.

560
00:35:23,900 --> 00:35:24,920
And kind of laughing, too.

561
00:35:24,960 --> 00:35:26,979
Yeah, he's laughing.

562
00:35:29,420 --> 00:35:30,928
What kind of laugh is that supposed to be?

563
00:35:30,953 --> 00:35:33,264
I mean, I can't tell, it's just too good.

564
00:35:33,940 --> 00:35:36,358
Do they really know what they're doing?

565
00:35:39,258 --> 00:35:41,539
Split

566
00:35:44,684 --> 00:35:47,039
I was torn between C and A

567
00:35:47,153 --> 00:35:49,153
But definitely A

568
00:35:50,348 --> 00:35:54,104
 Absolutely A

569
00:35:54,497 --> 00:35:56,925
Totally different

570
00:35:57,398 --> 00:36:01,092
I will bet on your confidence

571
00:36:01,700 --> 00:36:04,529
2 teams going to A

572
00:36:05,102 --> 00:36:11,014
Respecting Daichi's opinion, they head to Room A, where Kaminuma and Tendo are waiting.

573
00:36:13,604 --> 00:36:15,373
Welcome!

574
00:36:15,720 --> 00:36:17,594
Thank goodness.

575
00:36:18,599 --> 00:36:19,180
How was it?

576
00:36:19,350 --> 00:36:20,400
Was the gratin hard to judge?

577
00:36:20,447 --> 00:36:21,351
It was doria.

578
00:36:21,420 --> 00:36:22,140
Doria, doria.

579
00:36:22,280 --> 00:36:22,906
Doria.

580
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:27,944
That very first bite was insanely good.

581
00:36:27,970 --> 00:36:29,754
It was so good, like something out of a movie.

582
00:36:30,164 --> 00:36:34,602
Team Ordinary Hiromi Go and Team Ordinary Koda Kumi.

583
00:36:35,326 --> 00:36:37,143
You won't pick Hamada's dish, right?

584
00:36:37,168 --> 00:36:38,045
Right.

585
00:36:38,110 --> 00:36:39,205
We are not picking Hamada's.

586
00:36:39,230 --> 00:36:39,900
Yeah, of course not.

587
00:36:40,640 --> 00:36:41,999
Got it.

588
00:36:42,400 --> 00:36:46,279
The two who bragged they could definitely spot Chef Hamada's cooking.

589
00:36:46,300 --> 00:36:50,844
Can they really identify his flavor?

590
00:36:54,612 --> 00:36:56,260
The answers they give are...

591
00:36:56,420 --> 00:36:57,680
Ready...

592
00:36:58,380 --> 00:36:59,678
Whoa, C.

593
00:36:59,920 --> 00:37:01,121
They're split.

594
00:37:02,424 --> 00:37:04,142
They split.

595
00:37:04,167 --> 00:37:05,376
Oh man, what do we do?

596
00:37:05,400 --> 00:37:07,168
Hang on a second.

597
00:37:07,692 --> 00:37:10,555
Here we've got A, B, and C...

598
00:37:10,580 --> 00:37:13,130
For the first time, their answers are split three ways.

599
00:37:13,376 --> 00:37:15,674
So, for everyone watching at home,

600
00:37:15,700 --> 00:37:19,255
we'll now reveal the correct answer you've been waiting for.

601
00:37:19,280 --> 00:37:20,769
The chef with the correct dish is...

602
00:37:21,320 --> 00:37:22,953
This is it...

603
00:37:24,035 --> 00:37:25,677
C.

604
00:37:26,160 --> 00:37:28,713
The one I cooked was...

605
00:37:31,999 --> 00:37:35,174
Now we'll briefly introduce Chef Hamada's recipes for the beef stew

606
00:37:35,200 --> 00:37:38,520
and the doria.

607
00:37:39,060 --> 00:37:41,604
First, the beef stew.

608
00:37:42,405 --> 00:37:46,339
He pours in red wine like there's no tomorrow,

609
00:37:46,364 --> 00:37:51,698
then simmers it down for five days for a seriously committed dish.

610
00:37:51,798 --> 00:37:54,869
The secret ingredient is miso

611
00:37:55,200 --> 00:38:00,770
For a hidden accent, he adds hatcho miso, giving it a smooth, mellow finish.

612
00:38:01,445 --> 00:38:05,918
 For the doria, sauté the chicken in butter,

613
00:38:06,050 --> 00:38:08,642
then season it with consommé.

614
00:38:09,760 --> 00:38:13,096
Adjust the white sauce with salt and pepper,

615
00:38:13,380 --> 00:38:18,140
and finally heap on plenty of cheese, and it's done.

616
00:38:20,414 --> 00:38:22,185
I'm kind of happy about that.

617
00:38:22,210 --> 00:38:24,246
Better than ending up in a room with nobody else.

618
00:38:24,800 --> 00:38:25,972
I'd hate that.

619
00:38:26,220 --> 00:38:29,024
It's rough being stuck in here, it really is.

620
00:38:30,960 --> 00:38:33,125
Yeah, I really hated it.

621
00:38:33,150 --> 00:38:36,294
I just wanted someone, anyone, to come.

622
00:38:37,020 --> 00:38:38,979
But even if you're not alone, it's still a wrong answer.

623
00:38:39,010 --> 00:38:42,366
Both pairs drop down to second-rate.

624
00:38:43,821 --> 00:38:48,392
Meanwhile, Koda ended up choosing Hamada's B.

625
00:38:48,655 --> 00:38:52,596
The team's fate now rests with Hiromi Go.

626
00:38:52,621 --> 00:38:57,320
I was torn between A and C.

627
00:38:58,200 --> 00:39:02,406
If that's the case, I see 'A' as Hamachan's.

628
00:39:02,440 --> 00:39:03,599
No way it's C.

629
00:39:03,640 --> 00:39:06,722
I'm telling you, it can't be A.

630
00:39:08,120 --> 00:39:11,324
I'll pick C then?

631
00:39:11,359 --> 00:39:12,705
Or A, right?

632
00:39:12,730 --> 00:39:14,552
No, it's definitely not A.

633
00:39:15,440 --> 00:39:16,445
Amazing.

634
00:39:17,140 --> 00:39:18,608
Seriously amazing.

635
00:39:19,160 --> 00:39:21,344
Then let's go with C.

636
00:39:21,400 --> 00:39:22,251
Should we pick C?

637
00:39:23,140 --> 00:39:24,295
You really shouldn't rely on me

638
00:39:24,320 --> 00:39:26,375
No, at this point...

639
00:39:26,400 --> 00:39:28,232
I think we should bet on Hiromi.

640
00:39:28,257 --> 00:39:29,909
Koda-san, are you...

641
00:39:29,934 --> 00:39:32,745
Are you really talking casually to Hiromi Go?

642
00:39:32,770 --> 00:39:35,473
That just isn't right.

643
00:39:35,920 --> 00:39:37,498
Thanks to Go...

644
00:39:37,560 --> 00:39:39,445
Hot, hot, that's hot!
(Go's Livin la Vida Loca cover)

645
00:39:39,457 --> 00:39:42,278
They dodged Hamada and nailed the right answer!

646
00:39:42,290 --> 00:39:44,094
Go! Go! Go!

647
00:39:44,120 --> 00:39:45,516
An empty room...

648
00:39:47,880 --> 00:39:50,200
No, B's flavor was a bit too strong.

649
00:39:50,225 --> 00:39:53,245
Ah! Two votes for A.

650
00:39:53,278 --> 00:39:55,994
Huh? No way! I said A was Hama-chan's.

651
00:39:56,021 --> 00:39:57,461
Even if you say that, we still can't tell.

652
00:39:57,762 --> 00:40:00,013
Seriously? 'A' is Hama-chan's, you know.

653
00:40:00,038 --> 00:40:04,068
Yeah, that side dish felt kind of like a punk's cooking.

654
00:40:04,140 --> 00:40:06,837
He's pretty cool!

655
00:40:06,878 --> 00:40:10,315
They keep saying 'A' is Hama-chan's.

656
00:40:10,340 --> 00:40:11,320
But that can't be right, can it?

657
00:40:11,320 --> 00:40:12,315
No way, definitely not.

658
00:40:12,340 --> 00:40:14,478
A is the pro's dish.

659
00:40:14,503 --> 00:40:20,484
'A' is from Ox, the long-established Western-style restaurant run by the Sato brothers.

660
00:40:20,626 --> 00:40:25,802
Their beef stew is based on a special sauce that has been built up for over 50 years.

661
00:40:25,900 --> 00:40:30,399
They add tomato purée, wine, vegetables, and beef,

662
00:40:30,480 --> 00:40:35,593
then simmer it for over three hours to create a rich, concentrated flavor.

663
00:40:36,434 --> 00:40:41,963
As for the doria, they mix in supermarket-bought chicken and cook it together with the rice,

664
00:40:42,640 --> 00:40:48,964
top it with a cheesy, creamy béchamel sauce, and bake it to finish.

665
00:40:49,698 --> 00:40:53,875
If they pick Hamada here, they'll drop down to the 'look-alike' rank.

666
00:40:53,899 --> 00:40:56,854
Team '50-Minute Lover'.

667
00:40:57,021 --> 00:41:01,156
Mio-san makes desserts...

668
00:41:01,181 --> 00:41:02,501
at a professional level,

669
00:41:02,526 --> 00:41:06,532
he brought individually wrapped madeleines to the set, they looked like they were from a store

670
00:41:06,557 --> 00:41:07,488
He makes them himself?

671
00:41:07,513 --> 00:41:09,567
Yes, he actually bakes them.

672
00:41:09,592 --> 00:41:11,886
So when it comes to food,

673
00:41:11,898 --> 00:41:13,586
I won't

674
00:41:13,598 --> 00:41:16,540
make a mistake.

675
00:41:16,998 --> 00:41:20,466
Takahashi is absolutely confident in his cooking skills.

676
00:41:20,960 --> 00:41:23,502
He wants to nail the real Michelin dish,

677
00:41:23,610 --> 00:41:26,690
and somehow hang on to that second-rate rank.

678
00:41:27,560 --> 00:41:28,640
The answer they gave is...

679
00:41:28,720 --> 00:41:30,446
Ready, set...

680
00:41:33,459 --> 00:41:36,513
ahh... total split!

681
00:41:36,537 --> 00:41:38,576
Wow totally split

682
00:41:39,127 --> 00:41:43,023
Split!

683
00:41:43,035 --> 00:41:45,280
These 3...

684
00:41:45,292 --> 00:41:48,347
Which answer will they pick?

685
00:41:48,372 --> 00:41:51,008
Mitsuomi good job!

686
00:41:52,081 --> 00:41:54,523
He has the confidence about food but...

687
00:41:54,535 --> 00:41:56,299
dumb tongue

688
00:41:56,404 --> 00:41:58,760
A is definitely wrong

689
00:42:00,959 --> 00:42:05,245
I was thinking B is definitely not it.

690
00:42:05,980 --> 00:42:07,749
Tae, you went with A, right?

691
00:42:07,850 --> 00:42:10,094
I figured it had to be either A or C.

692
00:42:10,119 --> 00:42:11,920
We're all kind of ignoring B, aren't we?

693
00:42:11,920 --> 00:42:14,465
 Mitsuomi say something, will you?

694
00:42:14,490 --> 00:42:17,855
Then if it's between those, I guess C.

695
00:42:17,880 --> 00:42:20,571
Why won't you go for B, huh?

696
00:42:20,880 --> 00:42:22,154
All right, then...

697
00:42:23,140 --> 00:42:24,668
We'll go with C, please.

698
00:42:25,280 --> 00:42:28,345
Either way, they got it right. Nicely done.

699
00:42:28,600 --> 00:42:31,972
They were split between A, B, and C and it was a gamble,

700
00:42:31,984 --> 00:42:36,179
but they managed to converge on the correct answer and just barely stay in the second tier.

701
00:42:40,600 --> 00:42:42,099
The votes are split.

702
00:42:43,394 --> 00:42:45,074
No one picked B.

703
00:42:45,600 --> 00:42:47,695
I actually chose B.

704
00:42:48,560 --> 00:42:50,820
Right, Mitsuomi-san, you went with B.

705
00:42:51,447 --> 00:42:53,103
The B doria was really tasty, though.

706
00:42:53,140 --> 00:42:55,639
It was the best one.

707
00:42:56,160 --> 00:43:00,460
Our second-rate idols, Fruits-something-or-other.

708
00:43:01,847 --> 00:43:04,481
All right, Fruits...

709
00:43:04,710 --> 00:43:06,605
Zipper, yeah.

710
00:43:07,151 --> 00:43:08,686
Fruits Zipper, how are you feeling?

711
00:43:08,720 --> 00:43:12,240
When there's something to celebrate, our boss takes us to this super fancy place in Roppongi...

712
00:43:12,240 --> 00:43:15,392
Don't say that.

713
00:43:16,299 --> 00:43:19,063
You can't be going around saying stuff like that.

714
00:43:19,088 --> 00:43:21,694
So far, the ones who picked Chef Hamada are...

715
00:43:21,720 --> 00:43:24,335
only Koda Kumi and Mitsuomi Takahashi

716
00:43:25,040 --> 00:43:28,360
But still, no team has picked the 'absolutely no good' dish.

717
00:43:28,940 --> 00:43:30,397
Can they avoid it here as well

718
00:43:30,460 --> 00:43:31,654
and earn a reward from their boss,

719
00:43:31,680 --> 00:43:36,056
getting taken to a nice restaurant in Roppongi?

720
00:43:36,560 --> 00:43:38,052
Now, their answer is...

721
00:43:38,320 --> 00:43:39,797
Ready, and...

722
00:43:42,500 --> 00:43:45,735
