723
00:43:45,760 --> 00:43:50,135
So it's B... that's Hamada's dish right?

724
00:43:50,160 --> 00:43:52,339
That's really good.

725
00:43:54,400 --> 00:43:57,301
No way, does that actually happen?

726
00:43:57,326 --> 00:44:03,640
I felt like the natural sweetness and the tenderness of the meat were really high quality.

727
00:44:04,008 --> 00:44:07,154
These kids are so sweet.

728
00:44:07,180 --> 00:44:11,194
I thought B was the most properly made as a dish.

729
00:44:11,220 --> 00:44:13,295
Okay, then let's go with B.

730
00:44:13,320 --> 00:44:16,495
All right, we'll choose B.

731
00:44:16,520 --> 00:44:16,919
Okay.

732
00:44:17,040 --> 00:44:19,192
All right.

733
00:44:19,218 --> 00:44:21,960
Here it comes.

734
00:44:23,036 --> 00:44:25,298
Now you can open your first restaurant

735
00:44:25,684 --> 00:44:28,995
But A and C didn't seem all that shocked.

736
00:44:29,020 --> 00:44:29,762
Yeah, exactly.

737
00:44:29,840 --> 00:44:31,174
More like, 'Oh, is that so.'

738
00:44:31,200 --> 00:44:33,871
'Ahh, yeah, we picked that one...' kind of reaction.

739
00:44:34,560 --> 00:44:38,034
The group formerly known as Fruits Zipper, now Fruits Chuck

740
00:44:38,460 --> 00:44:42,550
