741
00:44:43,066 --> 00:44:45,575
Wait, hold on, that's bad!

742
00:44:45,600 --> 00:44:47,117
What do we do?

743
00:44:47,360 --> 00:44:48,407
You’ve got to be kidding.

744
00:44:48,507 --> 00:44:50,483
This is scary, seriously.

745
00:44:50,694 --> 00:44:51,455
Wait!

746
00:44:51,820 --> 00:44:53,643
Hey!

747
00:44:54,054 --> 00:44:56,284
This could be Hamada's food

748
00:44:56,326 --> 00:44:57,094
True.

749
00:44:57,294 --> 00:45:00,549
Can Team Yoshimoto hang on to their normal-celebrity status?

750
00:45:00,819 --> 00:45:02,900
If we survive this round, it’s huge.

751
00:45:02,940 --> 00:45:05,235
It really tests our teamwork too.

752
00:45:05,402 --> 00:45:08,305
I pretty much cook for myself every day.

753
00:45:09,431 --> 00:45:11,142
I cook a ton.

754
00:45:11,180 --> 00:45:13,075
Have you ever eaten Hamada’s cooking?

755
00:45:13,100 --> 00:45:13,624
Yeah!

756
00:45:13,840 --> 00:45:16,360
I had it when we did a show together.

757
00:45:16,426 --> 00:45:20,593
You can tell right away when a dish is missing love, you know?

758
00:45:20,617 --> 00:45:25,122
So if you feel like there’s no love in it, that one’s Hamada’s

759
00:45:27,720 --> 00:45:32,840
On the menu: the Batteries duo get doria, and Atsushi gets beef stew.

760
00:45:33,530 --> 00:45:38,434
Earlier, at the 8 strings round, Atsushi’s mistake knocked them out of top-rank status.

761
00:45:38,680 --> 00:45:44,299
As the senior, he can’t drag his juniors down any further.

762
00:45:44,320 --> 00:45:45,913
We’re supposed to guess which one is Hamada’s, right?

763
00:45:45,960 --> 00:45:48,427
No! You’re unbelievably dumb.

764
00:45:48,452 --> 00:45:50,842
What the hell are you talking about?

765
00:45:50,867 --> 00:45:52,502
So, what’s your answer?

766
00:45:52,710 --> 00:45:54,175
Ready, set...

767
00:45:54,920 --> 00:45:56,092
Huh?

768
00:45:56,400 --> 00:45:57,354
Whoa.

769
00:45:58,520 --> 00:46:00,265
This time Atsushi got it right.

770
00:46:00,290 --> 00:46:01,778
No, but this is…

771
00:46:02,110 --> 00:46:04,020
Everyone ends up going back and forth between A and C.

772
00:46:04,150 --> 00:46:05,711
It’s not B.

773
00:46:06,160 --> 00:46:08,298
Lively bunch.

774
00:46:10,124 --> 00:46:12,427
I think A is Hamada.

775
00:46:12,492 --> 00:46:14,214
It’s A isn’t it, Hamada?

776
00:46:14,240 --> 00:46:15,836
Hmm, that’s what it feels like.

777
00:46:15,884 --> 00:46:18,588
For me it’s overwhelmingly A, though.

778
00:46:19,000 --> 00:46:19,815
The beef stew?

779
00:46:19,840 --> 00:46:25,741
The meat quality in B, and how smooth the stew is...

780
00:46:26,300 --> 00:46:28,020
B… B is Hamada’s.

781
00:46:28,060 --> 00:46:30,100
